There are four problems with faking one's death. #1: Money. #2: Family and friends. #3: Means #4: Blocking investigation. #1: Money. This is the second most difficult one. You have to withdraw cash over a very long period of time in order for it to not be suspicious. I highly recommend withdrawing slightly more than needed for rent/utilities every month, and then stashing it somewhere. Remember that you'll need to keep it out of the way, so I suggest a geocache-type box (locked safe etc) somewhere that you'll know where it is. If legal in your country, you may also want to stock the box with firearms in case of an emergency. You see, the problem with suddenly withdrawing a bunch of cash and then "dying" is that it's very suspicious. No one just randomly dies after getting a bunch of cash. It's going to throw instant suspicion on your "death", and that's something that you don't want. The less investigation the better. A fairly common practice in the business of faking one's death is to take out a large life insurance policy on yourself a few years prior, using a fake name. This used to be easier; you could take it out a couple years early, fake your death, collect as your alter ego, and profit. However, in today's world, insurance companies require an SSN or a similar means of identification, meaning that you may have to hire someone to be the proxy or "mule" recipient of your policy. (Be sure that you trust them!) And a third sub-point: BE SURE THAT YOU HAVE ENOUGH MONEY!! Did you take out a really large insurance policy on yourself? Are you certain that you'll be able to live off of it for the rest of your life? Remember, most things in the USA that are money related do require an SSN. This means that you won't be able to take a job if something goes belly-up, unless it's a cash-under-the-table kind of deal. So MAKE. SURE. THAT. YOU. HAVE. ENOUGH. MONEY. Do budgets (on private devices that you store in your cashbox, of course.) Calculate traveling and eating and housing expenses. Where are you going to live? Hopefully another country.
